\chapter{Italian States} 

Italy was united when the Kingdom of Italy was created in 1861. Before unification the individual "States" had their own postal communications arrangements and issued their own stamps. The different entities are listed below and their stamps and postal history are dealt extensively in the sections that follow.

\begin{itemize}
  \item Lombardy-Venetia
  \item Dutchy of Modena
  \item Kingdom of Naples
  \item Neapolitan provinces
  \item Papal States
  \item Dutchy of Parma
  \item Romagna
  \item Sardinia
  \item Sicily
  \item Tuscany
\end{itemize}







                   